The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 Geneva, Sept.8: WTO director Pascal Lamy has said a global trade deal was within reach but political leaders needed to give a final push to complete the negotiations. He warned that the consequences of failure could be dire, saying protectionism historically paved the way to war, and that poor countries would feel slighted if the industrialised world continued to enjoy favours.

 Mumbai, Sept. 8: Essar Steel has announced a floor price of Rs 38 apiece for buying shares from its minority shareholders. This follows the companys decision to delist from the stock exchanges. The offer will open on September 14.

 Dalian, Sept. 8: China has stopped production of 18.4 mt of iron and steel in the first half of the year to reduce energy consumption and greenhouse gas emission.




